# Paths excluded from the coverage gate (regex over coverage-profile lines).
# Keep this list small and well-justified.

# Entry point — wiring, flag parsing, signal handling, no behaviour worth a test.
github.com/kfet/harborrs/cmd/harborrs/main.go

# Frontend static-check helper — invoked via `make lint-frontend`,
# not exercised by go test.
github.com/kfet/harborrs/scripts/lintfrontend/main.go

# End-to-end test package; exercised by `make e2e`, not unit tests.
^github.com/kfet/harborrs/e2e/

# Self-update: deep filesystem I/O error branches (chmod after create,
# rename atop running exe, io.Copy mid-stream, tar.Next post-header).
# Happy path + all classified errors (network, checksum, missing entry,
# bad gzip, managed paths) are covered; contriving the remaining
# kernel-level errors adds noise without informing the behaviour.
github.com/kfet/harborrs/internal/selfupdate/selfupdate.go
